node.text:
Sushi master Endo Kazutoshi looks at nine sushi scenes from popular TV shows and movies and rates them based on realism. 

He looks at "John Wick: Chapter 3 – Parabellum" (2019), "The Sopranos" S6 E1 (2006), "Gintama" episode 120 (2008), "Billions" S2E2 (2017), "East Side Sushi" (2014), "Isle of Dogs" (2018), "Samurai Gourmet" S1E7 (2017), "Dead Sushi" (2012), and "Madagascar" (2005). 
Endo is a third-generation sushi master specializing in the Edomae style of sushi, a technique particular to Tokyo. He was born in Yokohama and has been working in kitchens for 26 years. He opened Endo at the Rotunda, an omakase restaurant in the former BBC TV studios in White City, London, in 2018. The restaurant is famed for its 200-year-old hinoki wood counter and rice water imported from Endo's home town to maintain the perfect pH. He serves a 20-course sushi menu. In 2020, he opened the sushi restaurant Sumi in London's Notting Hill.

Find out more at https://www.endoatrotunda.com/

#Sushi #SushiMaking #JapaneseFood #MadagascarMovie #JohnWick3 #EndoKazutoshi

node.title: Sushi master rates 9 sushi scenes in movies and TV | How real is it

node.text:
Topped with dark chocolate icing on one half and vanilla icing on the other half, the black and white cookie is a delicious treat that can be found at grocery stores and delis all over the city.

But the cookies can vary quite a bit across regions. In the city, the cookie is known to be made flat on a denser cake with fondant icing. Meanwhile in upstate New York and Boston, the cookie is more dome-shaped and is made with a fluffier cake that’s topped with a buttercream frosting. 

We visit Zaro’s Bakery (@zarosfamilybakery), a company that ships its cookies nationwide, to get a behind-the-scenes look at the making process of the NYC style of the famous East Coast cookie.

Featuring @medhapedia

node.title: How Black and White Cookies Are Made In NYC

node.text:
Pastrami on rye has been a New York staple since the 1900s. They can be bought at old-school Jewish delis like @therealpastramiqueen. The cured meat was brought back in the late 19th and early 20th centuries when a wave of Eastern European immigrants came to the East Coast. Although delis like Pastrami Queen are nowadays a rarity, pastrami on rye is still a huge part of New York’s soul. The pastrami meat is essentially pickled, which was originally meant to preserve the meat. Pastrami can be cured or brined for 5 days to a whole week and is meant to be juicy and tender. Insider's @medhapedia  takes a closer look at how pastrami is nowadays prepped for NYC delis.

node.text:
Michael Phelps, who is now retired, shared his health regimen with GQ, and I decided to try it out. It was difficult to eat a salad every day, but I loved getting more sleep and eating more veggies. Overall, Phelps' routine helped me feel more energized and gave me a positive attitude.

Click the link in our bio to read more about Michael Phelps' routine.

(Credit: Insider)
#MichaelPhelps #DietPlans #Olympics2021

node.accessibility_caption: Photo collage showing vegetables and Michael Phelps with headline, "I tried eating, sleeping, and exercising the way Michael Phelps does in retirement, and it was surprisingly easy"

Photo collage showing spinach and smoothie with text, "I started every day with a smoothie or eggs, just like Phelps does. I had to set aside a chunk of time each morning to make the smoothie and eggs, but I realized I stayed fuller longer during the day thanks to the large, healthful breakfast."
Photo showing a salad with text, "Phelps said he and his family incorporates one salad into their diet every day. When I read that, I immediately got nervous because I've never been a fan of salads."

Photo showing vegetables with text, "I attempted to add more vegetables to my diet. All week long, I found recipes that turned these vegetables into delicious sides. With a well-balanced plate, I found myself eating less and feeling more full after dinner."

Photo showing a phone screen with alarms set with text, "Phelps also recommends getting 7 to 9 hours of sleep. I tried to do the same. I started noticing a positive change in my mood every morning when my alarm woke me up."

Photo showing the writer taking a break during a workout with text, "I tried to match Phelps' fitness routine, which involves HIIT training and cardio. As someone who rarely works out, HIIT training took a lot out of me."

Photo showing the writer drinking a smoothie with text, "I felt a positive change in my overall well-being at the end of the week. Phelps' routine is simple, and its effects completely changed my outlook on diet culture."
A graphic that shows an image of pasta and reads: Everything you need to know to make homemade pasta

node.text:
All you need to make homemade pasta are flour, eggs, and water. Fresh pasta dough can be cut into a variety of shapes, from lasagna sheets to pappardelle to ravioli. Rely on how the dough feels rather than strict measurements — you can always adjust as needed.

Click the link in our bio for more tips on making pasta from Amber Gibson.

(Credit: Getty Images/Shutterstock)

node.accessibility_caption: A graphic that shows an image of pasta and reads: Everything you need to know to make homemade pasta

A graphic that shows an image of pasta and reads: Making pasta from scratch is time-consuming but not as hard as you might think it is. It's a fun family activity with kids, or it can be relaxgin and meditative on your own

A graphic that shows an image of someone making pasta. It reads: The ingredients in homemade pasta are very simple — flour, egg, salt, oil, and flavorings/coloings — but each on contributes significantly to the final dish. For the best homemade pasts, use high quality-ingredients.
A graphic that reads: Additional materials: Medium bowl, wooden cutting board, fork, bench scraper, plastic wrap, semolina, (for dusting) pasta roller (optional), and rolling pin (optional).

A graphic that shows somone kneading dought that reads: generally aim for slightly less than one cup of flour per egg and adjust the final consistency with water or more flour. Plan on using one egg per person. Knead dough until it's smooth and uniform.

A graphich that shows somone rolling out pasta using a pasta roller. It reads: A tabletop pasta sheeter can roll out and cut your noodles quickly. To roll out dought at home, you can always use a rolling pun, but you may have trouble getting it thin enough. Pasta should be cooked for 30 seconds to 2 minutes according to chef adam berger.

A graphic that reads: Tips for the best homemade pasta: let yourself make a mess. You'll probably end up with flour all over your kitch. Accoepting it can ensure you have more fun enjoying the process. Practice makes perfect. Berger says a regular Pasta-making routine (several timese a month) is necessary to get the hang of it.

node.text:
Videos of chicken sandwiches at In-N-Out are going viral on TikTok, with users claiming that they’re hidden on the beloved chain’s “secret” menu.

But a spokesperson for the chain told Insider that the videos are fake to “attract attention,” and that there are no plans for the chain to wade into the ongoing fried-chicken sandwich wars between other fast-food giants.

Read the full story by clicking the link in our bio.

(Credit: andynot2021/TikTok)

Sushi master Endo Kazutoshi looks at nine sushi scenes from popular TV shows and movies and rates them based on realism. 

He looks at "John Wick: Chapter 3 – Parabellum" (2019), "The Sopranos" S6 E1 (2006), "Gintama" episode 120 (2008), "Billions" S2E2 (2017), "East Side Sushi" (2014), "Isle of Dogs" (2018), "Samurai Gourmet" S1E7 (2017), "Dead Sushi" (2012), and "Madagascar" (2005). 
Endo is a third-generation sushi master specializing in the Edomae style of sushi, a technique particular to Tokyo. He was born in Yokohama and has been working in kitchens for 26 years. He opened Endo at the Rotunda, an omakase restaurant in the former BBC TV studios in White City, London, in 2018. The restaurant is famed for its 200-year-old hinoki wood counter and rice water imported from Endo's home town to maintain the perfect pH. He serves a 20-course sushi menu. In 2020, he opened the sushi restaurant Sumi in London's Notting Hill.

Find out more at https://www.endoatrotunda.com/

At some point, everyone has likely had some iced coffee that tasted stale, bitter, and sour. That happens when hot coffee is allowed to slowly cool to room temperature. The key is to cool the coffee as quickly as possible, ideally while brewing.

And the great thing about iced coffee is that you don't need any new fancy equipment. Whatever brewing method you use at home can be used to make iced coffee! 

Read Insider’s Home & Kitchen instructions on how to make iced coffee with whatever brewing equipment you already have on hand at the link in our bio.

node.text:
Air fryers have become a popular addition to many kitchens.  The miniature convection ovens cook almost anything, including steak, roasted vegetables, and cookies. 

They are easy and quick to use since there is no need to heat up any water or oil with an air fryer.  The basket inside the air fryer guarantees that the food cooks evenly. 

Hot air is what "fries" the food in an air fryer.  The air spins around the oven, ensuring that the food gets perfectly cooked with a "fried" crispy texture. 

Click on the link in our bio to read more of Marisel Salazar's story. 

(Credit: Plan Shooting 2 / Imazins/Getty Images/Cavan Images/THEGIFT777/LauriPatterson)
#airfryer #cooking #food

Photo shows a blue food truck with the Kraft Mac & Cheese and Van Leeuwen logos on it. There is a line of people waiting in front of the truck. It is overlaid with text that reads: "People were lined up outside of the special truck covered in Van Leeuwen and Kraft logos. When I got my cup of ice cream, I immediately noticed its bright-yellow hue — the same color as the cheesy powder that comes in a box of Kraft Macaroni & Cheese, though the texture was wildly different."

Photo shows a cup of the bright yellow ice cream. It is overlaid with text that reads: "The first bite tasted exactly like a spoonful of smooth Kraft Macaroni & Cheese. It was a bit surprising at first to consume the taste of mac and cheese in a frozen form, but it was comforting and delicious in a way I didn't expect."

Photo shows the writer eating the ice cream. It is overlaid with text that reads: "As the ice cream hit the back of my tongue, the flavor softened, turning into a savory and sweet treat that made me want to keep eating it. However, the cheese-filled ice cream was incredibly rich, so I found myself feeling full after just a few bites."
